<body>
    <h1>Proxy API Guidelines</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>Proxies are components that have an interface like an API, but d=
o not contain any code implementation. They are used as passthroughs to act=
ual APIs that are on a separate host.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(=
23,43,77);">All outbound access to vendor service/&nbsp;API&nbsp; or an inb=
ound access by a partner is always through a proxy API that is hosted in We=
stpac Mesh API gateway .</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Vendor must supply a service speci=
fication/ contract in the form of Swagger / Open API definition (for Restfu=
l API's)&nbsp;or WSDL (for SOAP based Web services). The Proxy component al=
so should have</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.=
com.au/display/WDPIPAAS/Proxy+use+case+scenarios" rel=3D"nofollow">environm=
ent configuration and security policies</a>&nbsp;as per the&nbsp;<a href=3D=
"/display/MESH/Supported+Authentication">Supported Authentication</a></p>
<p>Different <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/=
repos/contracts/browse/examples" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">G=
olden Templates </a>are used for the different API Proxy use cases.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ProxyAPIGuidelines-ServiceProxy:OutboundaccesstoVendorAPI">Servic=
e Proxy: Outbound access to Vendor API</h3>
<p>For this use case where you need to consume either an external vendor AP=
I, or a non-Westpac Mesh internal API , you require a Service Proxy. Eg: MS=
 APIs / IBM Watson APIs etc&nbsp;</p>
<p>For a Service Proxy, you can use the <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse/templates/swagger.yaml" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Golden Template for a standard API<=
/a>, with the following considerations:</p>
<ul>
<li>As the resource definitions will follow what is specified in the vendor=
's API, the Proxy swagger does not need to strictly follow Westpac Mesh des=
ign guidelines. However some effort should be made to sanitise the swagger =
so it is readable and reusable for a broader audience.</li>
<li>x-headers which are mandatory for APIs running on Westpac Mesh can be r=
emoved. They should not be sent to external vendors. X-headers may be sent =
to non-Westpac Mesh internal APIs for logging/audit purposes.</li>
<li>'Vendor name' is suffixed to the title of the API to indicate it is a v=
endor Proxy&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><map id=3D"gliffy-map-1203279319-9032" name=3D"gliffy-map-1203279319-903=
2"></map></p>
<table width=3D"100%" class=3D"gliffy-macro-table">
